post_text:
The EV, Keota, Sigourney, and TC superintendents discussed the youth volleyball program. It was decided that each district is planning to minimize the use of the facilities (for the first 6 weeks, and re-evaluate as the school year progresses); this includes youth activities. It is saddening to say, but we will not have a youth volleyball league this year due to the schools' safety guidelines and precautions.

Please pass the message on to any others that may need to know, particularly the incoming 3rd graders and parents.

Donita Clarahan

post_text:
School Bus Driver

The Keota Community School District is looking for qualified School Bus Driver to drive a regular daily bus route starting the first day of the 2020-2021 School Year.

Requirements include: CDL Endorsement, School Bus Endorsement, Passenger Endorsement. Must complete the following, the district will help through this process, a Stop Training Course, must pass a DOT physical by a certified physician, pass a pre-employment drug test and background check. Subject to random drug and alcohol testing.

To Apply, please pick up an application at the district office or apply online through www.teachiowa.gov
by August 1, 2020.

post_text:
The Washington County Extension office is not able to do summer camps like we have done in the past. Instead we have FREE 4-H To Go bags full of STEM activities and adventures for the month of June for students in Kindergarten thru 6th grade. Each week your child would be getting a new bag of activities to complete and have fun with. Below you will find the themes of the 4 bags being distributed. You would pick the bags up at either one of the two drop off points for school lunches. Please considering picking up these FREE STEM bags full of fun and exciting adventures. Contact Crystial Wright - if you would like to participate! 319-863-3181 or by e-mail crystial.wright@keota.k12.ia.us.

4-H To Go Summer Bags
Bag 1: BLAST Off to Summer
Bag 2: Outside Adventures
Bag 3: Fun in the Sun
Bag 4: Adventures in Agriculture

Sincerely,
Diane Rinner-Youth Outreach Educator
Washington County Extension Office
319-653-4811

If these times do not work for you please contact Mr. K or myself and we will do our best to work with you. alex.klopfenstein@keota.k12.ia.us, crystial.wright@keota.k12.ia.us, office number 641-636-2323 or Crystial's cell 319-863-3181. We would like to have all items picked up by the end of this week if possible.

Just a reminder of the school meal program available free for any child 0 - 18 years of age. Pick up points are the school, Talleyrand, Knights of Columbus Hall, Dublin store, and Marilyn Sieren's driveway. All meals benefit the school lunch program and are state funded. Please sign up by 7am each day https://forms.gle/NWJ6vkyng2XA2nJf9

Thank you and we hope everyone is doing well. Hugs to you all.

post_text:
Parents,
As you know Governor Reynolds extended the school closure through April 30th. Mr. Klopfenstein and I have created and delivered expectations for staff during this extension. Keota Schools are adopting a Voluntary Continuous Learning Plan through April 30th. This means we do NOT have to make up the hours after April 13th.

Based on directives from the Iowa Department of Education, the only courses that are required for Keota students are credit recovery classes and concurrent enrollment classes through local community colleges.

Parade will start at 4:00. Starting at the Kewash Trailhead.

We can't wait to see you!

post_text:
Keota Parents/Families:

We will be offering meals starting this Wednesday, March 25th for all children ages 0-18. Meals will consist of breakfast and lunch foods. The form to sign up for meals will need to be filled out for every meal requested the night before or before 7:00am the morning of the meal requested. This helps our meal staff prepare the correct amount of meals.

We will be delivering meals to 4 different locations outside of the circle drive at the school. Those locations are Tallyrand, Dublin Store, Marilyn Sieren's driveway, and the KC Hall in Harper. Meals will be available at each location from 12:00-12:30pm daily until further notice. If you are at a location other than the school, please look for a school vehicle that will have the meals.

Thank you for your continued support and understanding. Go Eagles! #keotaeagles

post_text:
Parents please share with your students...

Keota Students,

I wanted to let you know that I am thinking about each and every one of you. I want each of you to know that your teachers, support staff, janitors, cooks, and all who work at school miss you. We know that this can be hard to understand and confusing, and that is okay. We are here to help like we would any other day.

We hope you take some time to relax and know that your parents/guardians are doing their best to help you too! Change is scary, but change makes us grow stronger. If you have any questions for me, you can have your parents call or email me or respond below this post and I will do my best to respond as quickly as I can. I want to be here to help each and every one of you.

Please take some time to play, be imaginative, or just sit and relax with a good book. I will continue to think about each of you! Take care and be awesome like I know each of you are!

Sincerely,
Mr. K

#keotaeagles

shared_text:
Angela Hearne Conrad is with Brooke Roth Vittetoe and Heather Jaeger.
January 25 at 7:27 PM ¬∑

I am SO proud of my ELP 6th graders! They placed 5th today out of 39 teams in the Future City Competition in Cedar Rapids. This is an AMAZING accomplishment, especially considering they were up against 7th and 8th graders and this was their VERY FIRST competition! They worked so hard for this and showed that small schools can still compete with the big dogs! Congratulations Cael, Gavin, and Jackson!

post_text:
Tomorrow is our BEACH DAY! We are so excited to celebrate tomorrow afternoon and to reward our students for all of the great ways they have shown one another how to SOARR during the first semester!

A couple of things...

Students are not allowed to wear their bathing suits only. They may do so over their clothes if they so choose, but it is NOT a requirement.

Students who do not follow the appropriate dress rules above will sit out of beach day until the appropriate attire can be attained.

Thank you in advance and we are looking forward to an AWESOME day!!

#keotaeagles #eaglesonthebeach

This morning at our Welcome Back assembly, we revealed some big news! Our students were so close to a Beach Day before break and once the December SOARR slips were added, they hit their goal!!

BEACH DAY 2020 will be this Friday, January 10th! We have a variety of activities planned to help reward our students!

We are so excited to kick off 2020 by bringing the beach to Keota! Great job students and keep up the great work!

We are SAFE!
We are ORGANIZED!
We are ACHIEVING!
We are RESPECTFUL!
We are RESPONSIBLE!

We are EXCITED FOR THE BEACH!

#keotaeagles #beachday2020 #eaglesonthebeach

If you are a preschool parent who does not have any other children in the concert, you may leave after the preschoolers perform. We understand this can be a late night for them at their young age.

We are looking forward to a great evening, the kids have worked very hard!
